🏆 Leaderboards
This is where I expanded the original concept quite a bit.

PinkiRaces works in two modes.

Local mode
Before Google Sheets is connected, everything already works.

It saves:

races

personal bests

results

leaderboard positions

locally.

So we can test the racing system immediately.

Global Google Sheets mode
Once you configure the included Apps Script:

const GOOGLE_SCRIPT_URL = "YOUR_DEPLOYED_EXEC_URL";
every valid result can be uploaded.

The leaderboard is filtered by exact:

race_id
So:

pinki_lsia_sprint
has its own leaderboard.

And:

pinki_mount_chiliad
has a completely separate leaderboard.

Leaderboard columns currently show:

#
Driver
Time
Vehicle
IRL Date
Your own row is highlighted.

🌍 Your races can also be global
This was an important change I made before handing it over.

Originally I had the Builder saving courses locally only.

That wouldn't fulfil:

"people can race on courses that I make"

properly.

So the backend now creates two Google Sheet tabs:

Courses
Stores your globally published races.

Results
Stores race finishes.

Every player's PinkiRaces app can download the global Courses catalogue when it opens.

That means you create:

Pinki Highway Sprint

publish it once...

…and everybody using PinkiRaces sees:

Pinki Highway Sprint

in their race selector.

🔐 Only you can publish races
The Apps Script contains:

const ADMIN_KEY = "CHANGE_THIS_TO_A_PRIVATE_PUBLISHER_KEY";
You set something private.

The Builder has:

Publisher Key

Then:

PUBLISH GLOBAL

The key is checked by Apps Script.

Ordinary players don't need it.

They can:

see races

race them

submit times

view leaderboards

But they can't publish or overwrite one of your official courses without your publisher key.

MINI mode
The MINI version displays live:

🏁 Race Name        CP 4/12       01:14.492

Vehicle: Deluxo     Next: 214m    Speed: 87
So someone can start the race, hit MINI, press ESC to give control back to GTA, and still keep a lightweight racing HUD visible.

Exactly the workflow we've been establishing with your other User Apps.

